 5. What are the differences between sqlite3 and mysql-connector-python?



 | Aspect       | sqlite3                    | mysql-connector-python                    |

 |  | -- | -- |

 | Server       | File-based (no server)     | Client-server (MySQL)                     |

 | Install      | Built-in Python            | pip install                               |

 | Connection   | sqlite3.connect('file.db') | mysql.connector.connect(host, user, pass) |

 | Concurrency  | Limited (file locks)       | High (server handles)                     |

 | Scale        | Small apps (<1GB)          | Enterprise (100GB+)                       |

 | Setup        | Zero-config                | Server + users                            |

 | Transactions | Implicit                   | Explicit modes                            |

 | Network      | Local only                 | Remote access                             |

